review_id:
I'm in Coffeyville for the week. As I live in Seattle coffee is a staple part of my diet one of the first things I hunt down when on the road. This place would be a hit in Seattle. They serve a great tasting, freshly roasted coffee and good food. The breakfast sandwich was excellent. It has a soothing old-wood vibe with a large layout that works for people looking to catch up on work emails, students, folks wanting to meet up, or locals enjoying their routine. Staff were really nice and attentive.

It also, looks like it's run by a young couple. So If you're traveling this way head in there, try it out and support the local business.

review_id: Friendly staff! I drink my coffee black, as you should :) and their medium roast was perfect. Not too acidic and not to weak. The lemon/blueberry scone was pretty good too!

review_id: Coffee lovers, Terebinth is a must for you!  The only place around for third wave coffee and the best!! Roasted and served fresh - never old or stale.  Also, fresh baked scones and fabulous lunch specials. Roasted turkey on Fridays is better than any turkey I've ever had. Also offer sourdough as a bread option and lactose free milk options as well.

review_id: Avoid this coffee shop. This coffee shop is inside the Hotel Theodore. First morning we went and everything was great. Following day we went because it's as the same barista with salt & pepper hair, she got flustered when I ordered 4 lattes. Then she was touching the pastries with her bare hands, after touching the register & dirty plates from other customers. She seemed short tempered and not able to handle multiple drink orders. Then she rang us up incorrectly and when I mentioned that the total doesn't add up her response was "I have a line" customer service was definitely not there and after her touching the food with her bare hands that was the last straw. In addition when I was stating how much syrup I wanted in my lattes she responded with I don't care I will just make it sweet. She also touch's the inside of the coffee cups with her hands. It's pretty disgusting. The hotel needs to retrain her or replace her. She should not be servicing the public with the lack of proper food/beverage handling.
